Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: attrs-mek
Version: 0.0.1
Summary: Clean nested deserialization for attrs
Home-page: https://www.attrs.org/
Author: Alex Rudolph
License: MIT
Description: # Hello
        
        this is my package
        
        here are some examples
        
        # Easy example
        
        ```python
        from attrs_mek import mek
        
        person = {"name": "Mek", "age": 0}
        
        
        @mek
        class Person:
            name: str
            age: int
        
        
        mek_person = Person.from_dict(person)
        # Person(name="Mek", age=0)
        ```
        
        some description
        
        # Example 2
        
        hello
        
        ```python
        from attrs_mek import mek, Key
        
        person = {"person": {"name": "Mek", "age": 0}}
        
        
        @mek
        class Person:
            person: Key
            name: str
            age: int
        
        
        mek_person = Person.from_dict(person)
        # Person(name="Mek" age=0)
        ```
        
        heres what's happening
        
        ```python
        from datetime import datetime
        from attrs.validators import instance_of
        from attrs_mek import mek, Key, Value
        
        person = {
            "person": {"name": "Mek", "age": 0},
            "meta": {"created": {"date": "2022/2/19"}},
        }
        
        
        def validate(cls, fields):
            return [f.evolve(validator=instance_of(f.type)) for f in fields]
        
        
        @mek(frozen=True, field_transformer=validate)
        class Person:
            person: Key
            name: str
            age: int
        
            meta_created: Key
            date: datetime = Value()
        
            @date.converter
            def date_converter(val):
                return datetime.strptime(val, "%Y/%m/%d")
        
        
        mek_person = Person.from_dict(person)
        # Person(name='Mek', age=0, created=datetime.datetime(2022, 2, 19, 0, 0))
        ```
        
        include attrs stuff
